              Can't we do a bit better than &quot;a coin flip&quot; determines an El Nino or a La Nina?<br /><br />There is SOME collection of forcing variables  that lead to one or the other. And not knowing those variables and the temperature of the Pacific appears to have a pretty large impact on our ability to predict atmospheric temperatures.

              

              
              
            </div>
