              Unfortunately this entire topic has turned in to a religion.  There should be no &quot;sides&quot; on this topic.  Here's a question for both sides of this debate.  <br /><br />As a believer in human based global climate warming, would you celebrate scientific discovery that the planet is, in fact not in such dire straights as you previously believed?<br /><br />As a skeptic of human influenced climate warming, under any circumstance would you embrace mitigation of human forcing on climate if enough scientific evidence was available to satisfy your objectivity?<br /><br />I don't think people that lean hard in either direction are willing to embrace those scenarios.   Too bad you people are in charge both science (funding) and policy (politics).  It's big damned mess.

              

              
              
